A Three Tier System:

Three-tier architecture is a client server architecture where presentation, domain logic and data management layers are physically separate. This gives the option of modifying a particular layer, instead of modifying the entire application.



A typical three tier in blocks.

At this point we can talk about cloud computing.

Introduction to Cloud

Imagine a world where you only have to pay money to gather resources.

And you do not have to physically possess it.

And you can increase or decrease the resources on demand.

And you have a list of resources to choose from and use.

And the freedom to switch to other category of resources immediately.

And you can do all of these only by writing **scripts,** no datacenter. This is cloud.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

It is a service which provides us resources on demand, which we can use to write our Application.

 A diagram showing three main categories of Services offered by Cloud vendors.



Categories of Cloud Computing Services

1. **IaaS(Infrastructure as a service):** The most basic kind of cloud service which aims at providing replacement of the physical infrastructure on demand. This category broadly covers Compute/Virtual Machines, Block Device/Physical data storage and Network components. Generally it lays the foundation to host the platform.
2. **Paas(Platform as a services):** Services at this category provides software engineers development environment, tools which can be used to build applications. This categories covers softwares, databases, User &amp; role management, Queuing systems, run times etc. Generally it lays the foundation to develop and host the application.
3. **Saas(Software as a service):** Services at this category provides built softwares on demand. Where generally developer customizes the softwares as per the organization&#39;s needs. Salesforce is a good example of SaaS.

Major cloud service providers.

1. **AWS:** Is a collection of cloud computing services, also called web services, that make up a cloud-computing platform offered by amazon.com. These services operate from 12 geographical regions across the world. The most central and well-known of these services arguably include Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud, also known as &quot;EC2&quot;.
2. **Azure:** Microsoft Azure is a cloud computing platform and infrastructure, created by Microsoft, for building, deploying and managing applications and services through a global network of Microsoft-managed and Microsoft partner hosted datacenters. It provides both PaaS and IaaS services and supports many different programming languages, tools and frameworks, including both Microsoft-specific and third-party software and systems.
3. **Cloud Platform:** Google Cloud Platform is a cloud computing platform by Google that offers hosting on the same supporting infrastructure that Google uses internally for end-user products like Google Search and YouTube. Cloud Platform provides developer products to build a range of programs from simple websites to complex applications.
4. **Rackspace:** The Rackspace Cloud is a set of cloud computing products and services billed on a utility computing basis from the US-based company Rackspace. Offerings include web application hosting or platform as a service, Cloud Storage, virtual private server, load balancers, databases, backup, and monitoring.
5. **IBM Smart Cloud:** IBM cloud includes infrastructure as a service (IaaS), software as a service (SaaS) and platform as a service (PaaS) offered through public, private and hybrid cloud delivery models, in addition to the components that make up those clouds.

Wondering, how cloud service provider achieves such degree of flexibility?

Most of the resources that we get from cloud is virtualized. Which means they are not real but they act like real with the help of softwares commonly called hypervisors. The computer, network resources, the disk volumes are presented to us through the virtualized layer. Since it is software, it is managed efficiently. Wiki for virtualization [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virtualization](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virtualization)

Conclusion.

There are various Cloud service providers each with their own set of advantage over the other in terms of billing, performance, reliability, scalability, usability etc. It is very essential to select the right cloud service provided based on the organization&#39;s need which may vary from time to time.

The main advantage cloud services are flexibility, pay per usage, security, easy to manage APIs, cut down procurement delays etc.

Now with this in our mind we would now focus on learning AWS (Amazon Web Services).
